RACE.RACE_TEXT: Grand National Timber S. GRAND NATIONAL RACE 1 3 1/4M Timber CR: N/A. Stakes Purse 30000. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. To be ridden by amateur riders acceptable to the race committee. Five-year-olds, 160 lbs.; older, 165 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MONBEG STREAM (IRE) tracked the leader through the first half of the chase, top pair went clear of the group heading towards the barn, always near the front, sent to the drive after the final jump, went clear of rival through the wire. RENEGADE RIVER took the lead across the road, always on or near the front, stayed with rival through the final two fences, conceded stubbornly in the final furlong. SHOOTIST raced in the middle of the pack, could never sustain a bid to catch top pair, clear for the show under the line. WITHOUTMOREADO (IRE) raced off the pace through out, one paced , could not close gap through the final jumps. ROYAL RUSE raced off the pace, had no late kick, through the stretch. MASTER SEVILLE slow into stride, never factored through the final furlong. OUR FRIEND (IRE) fell soon after the start.

ENTRY.NAME: Master Seville
ENTRY.COMMENT: away slow, never factored

ENTRY.NAME: Monbeg Stream (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leader early on, went clear driving final furlong

ENTRY.NAME: Withoutmoreado (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: raced off the pace, never a threat through final jumps

ENTRY.NAME: Our Friend (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: fell early on

ENTRY.NAME: Shootist
ENTRY.COMMENT: raced middle pack, out quickened by top pair, held show

ENTRY.NAME: Renegade River
ENTRY.COMMENT: early leader, always in close pursuit, conceded final furlong

ENTRY.NAME: Royal Ruse
ENTRY.COMMENT: raced off the pace, no late gain

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRAND NATIONAL RACE 2 3M Timber CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 12500. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON OVER TIMBER. To be ridden by amateur riders acceptable to the race committee. Five-year-olds, 160 lbs.; older, 165 lbs. No rider allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOGEY'S IMAGE took control early, stayed clear of rivals through out the chase, still in control into the final jumps, fended off foes under a steady drive. THE BUTLER YATES (IRE) raced off the early pace, found good footing in the middle of the pack, cleared final jumps, went under a drive, angled inside rival and gained the place. RHYTHMIA unhurried through the first half of the race, inched into contention through the final jumps, stayed on well, conceded the place in the final furlong. DRUID'S ALTAR (IRE) pulled up and did not finish. PROFITEER pulled up and did not finish. SHOOTIN THE BREEZE lost rider early at the second fence. HERO'S RETURN slipped on a turn and fell.

ENTRY.NAME: The Butler Yates (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked early, raced middle pack, late rush, gained second late

ENTRY.NAME: Druid's Altar (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: pulled up

ENTRY.NAME: Rhythmia
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried early, inched closer middle stage, stayed on well

ENTRY.NAME: Bogey's Image
ENTRY.OWNER: Colhoun Daniel O'Donovan Achsah and Goolsby Harvey
ENTRY.COMMENT: took control after first jump, stayed clear under a drive

ENTRY.NAME: Profiteer
ENTRY.COMMENT: pulled up

ENTRY.NAME: Shootin the Breeze
ENTRY.COMMENT: lost rider early at fence two

ENTRY.NAME: Hero's Return
ENTRY.COMMENT: slipped on turn, fell

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRAND NATIONAL RACE 3 3 1/4M Timber CR: N/A. Allowance Purse 17500. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OVER TIMBER. To be ridden by amateur riders acceptable to the race committee. Five-year-olds, 165 lbs.; older, 170 lbs. Non-winners over timber, allowed 8 lbs. No rider allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GREAT ROAD sent forward after the start, stayed well clear of rival through the middle stages of the race, came under pressure through the final hill, held on late under a heavy drive. BLACKHALL (IRE) tracked off the early leader, traveled well through the middle stages of the race, surged into contention nearing the final jump, could not reel in leader, finished well clear for the place. ROCKET STAR RED raced off the pace early on, could not quicken with top pair through the final jumps, evenly under the wire. HILL TIE set the pace across the road, unable to keep up the tempo through the middle stages, faded through the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Great Road
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent forward after first jump, held off rivals through the wire

ENTRY.NAME: Blackhall (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked off pace, surged late, could not reel in leader

ENTRY.NAME: Hill Tie
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace setter across the road, faded through the stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Rocket Star Red
ENTRY.COMMENT: raced off the pace, evenly through the stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRAND NATIONAL RACE 4 3M Timber CR: N/A. Allowance Purse 10000. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A TIMBER OR HURDLE STAKES IN 2022-2023. To be ridden by apprentice riders. 170 lbs. Non-winners of two races over timber, allowed 5 lbs.; of a race, 10 lbs. Riders who have never won a race, allowed 5 lbs. No other rider allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHOSEN MATE (IRE) sent to the front, controlled the tempo through out the contest, when asked to quicken kicked clear under a steady drive. FLETCHED found good position through out the chase, handled the jumps while racing off the solo leader, took a run entering the stretch, could not catch that rival, clearly second best today. RAKHAA (GB) raced middle pack through the first part of the race, inched up in contention headed to the barn, could not sustain bid, finished evenly through the wire. HUYANA slow into stride, never a threat to the leaders. IT'S NOTHING pulled up.

ENTRY.NAME: Fletched
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked solo leader through out, second best today

ENTRY.NAME: Huyana
ENTRY.COMMENT: slow into stride, never a threat

ENTRY.NAME: Chosen Mate (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: went clear from the start, quickened when asked, won driving

ENTRY.NAME: It's Nothing
